{
  "texts": [
    "They also mandate play (which we return to later in more detail).",
    "Research has shown that because agents find pleasure in reducing manageable uncertainty, they are attracted to just-uncertain-enough environments: the ones that offer such opportunities (see for example Kashdan & Steger 2007; Gottlieb et al. 2014; Kidd & Hayden 2015; Gottlieb & Oudeyer 2018; Van de Cruys 2017).",
    "AIF learning can be cast as the development of generative models that enable the realisation of expectations through sensorimotor engagement with the environment (Friston et al., 2016; Parr et al., 2022).",
    "Sensorimotor engagements maintain control over important physiological setpoints and, when combined with affordances that are opportunities for highly expected actions (e.g., eating, drinking), become meaningful for the agent.",
    "In this sense, AIF learning is highly active."
  ]
}